See below</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>r-3940561426.7481130c10b176</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Other academic audiences (collaborators, peers etc.)</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:year>2012</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Medieval Toursim</gtr:description><gtr:form>A magazine, newsletter or online publication</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>International</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>9EE9A4E1-526E-4AB6-BF2A-A8143CF97ED1</gtr:id><gtr:impact>This was an interview on my research by the BBC History Magazine, associated with an article published in its July 2012 issue, and which was made available via podcast at: http://cdn.bbcmagazinesbristol.com/bbchistory/audio/HistoryExtra_19thJul12.mp3 



